						<summary>

						<p>A pillar of the verandah round the same shrine.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Vīrarājēndradēva: Year 29 = 1235-36 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift of land made by a certain merchant named Marudanmudali <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vaṇikachakkaravartti of Muṭṭam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Amarabhuyaṅkaranallūr in Peru-nāḍu to provide for food-offerings to the deity Avināśi Āḷuḍaiyār Kūttāḍuvār. </p>						

